<br>
&quot;That sounds excellent, Varia.  We have a very good smith but she is aging and finds it more and more difficult to keep up with our needs.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Chiara gives a slight smirk. &quot;She'll have to protest for pride's sake that she's been smithing since before I was born and doesn't need any help, but secretly she'll be glad of it.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Chiara looks around briefly, noting the differences between Chadesia and her home.  She sees some flowers Baily would love, but knows they'd be in bad shape by the time she got them to the Caucasus Mountains.<br>
